<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="423" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,152,791]" pageId="22" pageNumber="423">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,152,179]" pageId="22" pageNumber="423">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Imago distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Pungeler" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[622,728,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Sagarriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="423" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="libyssa">
<emphasis box="[622,728,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="423">S. libyssa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the golden orange-ochre forewing upperside, sprinkled with black dots, and that of the hindwing, which fades from pale orange to dark-brown in males and from pale yellow to brown in females. The male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sagarra" authorityYear="1924" box="[635,727,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Coscinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="423" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="romei">
<emphasis box="[635,727,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="423">S. romei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ from those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Pungeler" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[962,1068,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Sagarriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="423" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="libyssa">
<emphasis box="[962,1068,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="423">S. libyssa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the medially slightly widened uncus, the roundly convex dorsal valva edge (obtuse angle in central dorsal valva margin in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Pungeler" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[1199,1306,261,287]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Sagarriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="423" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="libyssa">
<emphasis box="[1199,1306,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="423">S. libyssa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the wider opening between cucullus and subapical process on the ventral edge of the valva, the evenly rounded coecum of the aedeagus, and in the female genitalia by the absence of distinct signa and a fully membranous ductus seminalis.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="23" lastPageNumber="424" pageId="22" pageNumber="423" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,152,791]" pageId="22" pageNumber="423">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,587,368,395]" pageId="22" pageNumber="423">
Description. Imago (
<figureCitation box="[442,573,368,395]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–18" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1729,1754]" captionTargetBox="[232,1353,314,1662]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[227,1360,311,1666]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 9–18. 9. C. chrysocephala, male, Sierra Cabrera, Turre,Almería, (Spain) (coll. RMV); 10. C. chrysocephala, female, El Abalario, Huelva, (Spain) (coll. RMV); 11. C. mariarosae, male, Coll de Reis, Nus de sa Corbata, Escorca, Mallorca, Balears, (Spain) (coll. RMV); 12. C. mariarosae, female, Coll de Reis, Nus de sa Corbata, Escorca, Mallorca, Balears, (Spain) (coll. RMV); 13. S. libyssa caligans, male, Bronte, Etna, Sicilia, (Italy) (coll. RMV); 14. S. libyssa caligans, female, Bronte, Etna, Sicilia, (Italy) (coll. RMV); 15. S. libyssa liouvillei, male, Mischliffen, Middle Atlas, (Morocco) (coll. RMV); 16. S. libyssa liouvillei, female, Mischliffen, Middle Atlas, (Morocco) (coll. RMV); 17. S. romei, male, Val de Falcones, La Retuerta, Zaragoza, (Spain) (coll. RMV); 18. S. romei, female, Val de Falcones, La Retuerta, Zaragoza, (Spain) (coll. RMV)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3246052/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="423">Figs 17–18</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
Average wingspan (males) 
<quantity box="[898,998,368,395]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.56" pageId="22" pageNumber="423" unit="mm" value="25.6">25.6 mm</quantity>
(n = 10; 
<quantity box="[1100,1225,369,395]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" metricValueMax="2.9" metricValueMin="2.3" pageId="22" pageNumber="423" unit="mm" value="26.0" valueMax="29.0" valueMin="23.0">23–29 mm</quantity>
); (females) 19.6 (n = 10; 16–22). Upper surface of forewings golden orange-ochre, dusted with a scattering of fine black dots over the entire surface, more densely on the central part of the costa. Upper surface of hindwings in males pale orange, fading into dark brown towards tip and termen; in females costal area brown, fading into pale yellow towards dorsum. Considerable sexual dimorphism, females having a more voluminous abdomen and narrower, apically more pointed wings.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,152,791]" pageId="22" pageNumber="423">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,423,584,611]" pageId="22" pageNumber="423">
