).
</emphasis>
Valvae of male genitalia apically with a strongly pointed, hook-shaped cucullus, and with a triangular process subapically on the ventral edge; cucullus and subapical process together giving the impression of a “crab claw”. Aedeagus cylindrical with an evenly rounded coecum; numerous small spinules (cornuti) on the vesica in the posterior end. In the female genitalia, the papillae anales and segment VIII are relatively large in comparison with the copulatory tract. Ductus bursae short, with a T- or Y-shaped sclerite along the ventral side; ductus seminalis membranous; bursa copulatrix membranous apart from a few diffuse sclerotisations.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3246062/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="423" startId="22.[151,250,1781,1806]" targetBox="[172,1423,819,1710]" targetPageId="22">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,1781,1842]" pageId="22" pageNumber="423">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,281,1781,1806]" pageId="22" pageNumber="423">FIGURE 36</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sagarra" authorityYear="1924" box="[293,376,1782,1805]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Coscinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="423" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="romei">
<emphasis box="[293,376,1782,1805]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="423">S. romei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, male and female genitalia, gen. prep. 5726JG m. La Retuerta, Zaragoza, (Spain), 5708JG f. La Retuerta, Zaragoza, (Spain).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,1887,2022]" lastBlockId="23.[151,1437,153,971]" lastPageId="23" lastPageNumber="424" pageId="22" pageNumber="423">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,510,1887,1914]" pageId="22" pageNumber="423">
Immature stages (
<figureCitation box="[413,497,1887,1914]" captionStart="FIGURE 49" captionStartId="32.[151,250,989,1014]" captionTargetBox="[151,1267,181,932]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[151,1267,181,932]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURE 49. Immature state Sagarriella romei (picture MH)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3246082/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="423">Fig. 49</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
Last instar larva measures 
<quantity box="[814,938,1888,1914]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.6" pageId="22" pageNumber="423" unit="mm" value="18.0" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="16.0">16–20 mm</quantity>
. Head capsule dark brown. Dorsal area up to verruca L1 dark brown, then up to verruca L3 brown to dark orange. Dorsal central area with a narrow white line; ventral surface light brown to light grey; verruca D1, D2, SD1, L1, L2, L3 dark brown; thoracic legs with translucent femur, straw-coloured tibia, dark brown tarsus and light brown nail; abdominal prolegs with 9 to 10 larger nails. Pupa bright reddish brown that of male straight, that of female slightly tilted ventrally; antennae not touching distally, tips of pterothecae touching in a curved way.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,153,971]" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,388,225,251]" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">Molecular data.</emphasis>
Intraspecific uncorrected p-distances of the COI Barcode sequences range from 0% to 0.22%, with a mean of 0.11% (n = 4). The nearest interspecific neighbour is 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Pungeler" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[935,1043,261,287]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Sagarriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="libyssa">
<emphasis box="[935,1043,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">S. libyssa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with an uncorrected p-distance of 5.62–6.26%. GenBank accession numbers of the four partial COI sequences are 
<accessionNumber box="[1060,1189,296,323]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/MH688112" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">MH688112</accessionNumber>
– 
<accessionNumber box="[1203,1331,296,323]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/MH688115" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">MH688115</accessionNumber>
(see also 
<tableCitation box="[151,237,333,359]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,239,153,177]" captionTargetBox="[166,1410,190,1977]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="TABLE 2. Genetic data of Coscinia genus group specimens newly investigated in this study." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/3C8EEAA19F2B1C30FF506084793F3ECC" pageId="23" pageNumber="424" tableUuid="3C8EEAA19F2B1C30FF506084793F3ECC">Table 2</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,153,971]" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">
Sequencing of the nuclear wingless gene was successful with two samples, which have identical nucleotide sequences. The minimum interspecific p-distance is 2.39% to 
<taxonomicName box="[849,951,405,431]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Spiris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="striata">
<emphasis box="[849,951,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">S. striata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Staudinger" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[1006,1154,405,431]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Spiris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bipunctata">
<emphasis box="[1006,1154,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">S. bipunctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; comparison of wingless sequences with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Pungeler" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[329,435,441,467]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Sagarriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="libyssa">
<emphasis box="[329,435,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">S. libyssa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was not possible as sequencing of this marker was not successful in this taxon. GenBank accession numbers of the two partial wingless sequences are 
<accessionNumber box="[835,963,476,503]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/MH688151" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">MH688151</accessionNumber>
and 
<accessionNumber box="[1018,1151,476,503]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/MH688152" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">MH688152</accessionNumber>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,153,971]" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">
In the phylogenetic results, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sagarra" authorityYear="1924" box="[514,607,513,539]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Coscinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="romei">
<emphasis box="[514,607,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">S. romei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is strongly supported as monophyletic (1.00 PP, 100% BS), and strongly (1.00 PP) to moderately (83% BS) supported sister to the congeneric 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Pungeler" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[927,1033,549,575]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Sagarriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="libyssa">
<emphasis box="[927,1033,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">S. libyssa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="424" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,153,971]" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,584,611]" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">Biology.</emphasis>
Univoltine, imagines flying in a single extended generation from late August to mid-October, depending on the locality. The males are active during the day and especially before twilight. Both sexes are attracted at night to artificial light. The females are incapable of long flights due to their bulky abdomen and their relatively small wing surface, so they tend to remain perched on the stems of grasses. The larvae feed on different species of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,209,729,755]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Stipa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="23" pageNumber="424" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,209,729,755]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">Stipa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barnhart" authorityYear="1895" baseAuthorityName="R.Br." box="[223,321,729,755]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="23" pageNumber="424" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Poaceae</taxonomicName>
), and possibly also on 
<taxonomicName box="[570,690,729,755]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Lavandula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="23" pageNumber="424" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[570,690,729,755]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">Lavandula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[742,876,730,755]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Rosmarinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="23" pageNumber="424" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[742,876,730,755]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">Rosmarinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[889,1014,729,756]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="23" pageNumber="424" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Lamiaceae</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Ylla, J. &amp; Macia, R. &amp; Gaston, F. J." box="[1036,1214,729,755]" pageId="23" pageNumber="424" refId="ref27969" refString="Ylla, J., Macia, R. &amp; Gaston, F. J. (2010) Manual de identificacion y guia de campo de los Arctidos de la Peninsula Iberica y Baleares. Arganda Editio, Barcelona, 290 pp." type="book" year="2010">
Ylla 
<emphasis box="[1092,1147,729,755]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
). Additional data on the biology can be found in García-Barros (1992).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="424" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,153,971]" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,464,800,827]" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">
Distribution (
<figureCitation box="[363,451,800,827]" captionStart="FIGURE 58" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1235,1260]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[238,1349,299,1118]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 58. Distribution map of S. romei." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3385774/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">Fig. 58</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
Endemic to the Iberian Peninsula, typical of steppe arid zones, at altitudes between 200 and 
<quantity box="[247,335,837,863]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="23" pageNumber="424" unit="m" value="1200.0">1200 m</quantity>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Sagarra" baseAuthorityYear="1924" box="[346,544,837,863]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Sagarriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="romei">
<emphasis box="[346,544,837,863]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">Sagarriella romei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seems to prefer stony localities in sunny open places rich in 
<taxonomicName box="[1224,1429,837,863]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="23" pageNumber="424" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="coccifera">
<emphasis box="[1224,1429,837,863]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">Quercus coccifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[151,344,873,899]" class="Pinopsida" family="Cupressaceae" genus="Juniperus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="23" pageNumber="424" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sabina">
<emphasis box="[151,344,873,899]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">Juniperus sabina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[357,444,873,899]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Thymus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[357,444,873,899]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">Thymus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Ylla et al. 2010)" authorityName="Ylla" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Ylla et al." baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[499,836,873,899]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Rosmarinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="23" pageNumber="424" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[499,633,874,899]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">Rosmarinus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ylla, J. &amp; Macia, R. &amp; Gaston, F. J." box="[647,828,873,899]" pageId="23" pageNumber="424" refId="ref27969" refString="Ylla, J., Macia, R. &amp; Gaston, F. J. (2010) Manual de identificacion y guia de campo de los Arctidos de la Peninsula Iberica y Baleares. Arganda Editio, Barcelona, 290 pp." type="book" year="2010">
Ylla 
<emphasis box="[704,760,873,899]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="424" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,153,971]" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,909,935]" pageId="23" pageNumber="424">Remarks.</emphasis>
The correct spelling of the species epithet is 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Macià &amp; Mally &amp; Ylla &amp; Gastón &amp; Huertas" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Sagarra" baseAuthorityYear="1924" box="[825,889,910,935]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Sagarriella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="romei">
